synopses.synopsis: Challenge of the Yukon was the third major juvenile adventure series to come out of George W. Trendle's Detroit radio mill and make the national networks. The Lone Ranger had been a western favorite since 1933; The Green Hornet had been battling urban corruption since 1938. Challenge took its listeners to the wild north and quickly endeared itself to young listeners everywhere. - On the Air: The Encyclopedia of Old-Time Radio by John Dunning
